h eating", "yield_notes": "Highly valued commercial variety in Dominican production", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Cuban Fiberless (Guanabana Sin Fibre) 🏆", "slug": "cuban-fiberless-guanabana-sin-fibre", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 12, "origin": "Santiago de las Vegas Agricultural Experiment Station, Cuba (1920s-1950s)", "traits": "Medium-sized, yellow-green fruit, distinctive bluish-green foliage", "flesh_fruit": "FIBERLESS or very low fiber content (defining characteristic), smooth texture, less acid than typical varieties", "yield_notes": "Vegetatively propagated clone ensures consistent quality", "growing_notes": "HEIRLOOM STATUS - historic Cuban selection from 1920s-1950s era. Vegetatively propagated superior clone. Distinctive bluish-green foliage allows identification. Fiberless characteristic highly valued for processing and fresh consumption. Cuban agricultural expertise in tropical fruit improvement. Made its way to Florida in 1959. Ideal for Tropical monsoon tropical climate. Excellent for ice cream, smoothies, and juice production due to smooth texture.", "availability": "May be available through Cuban germplasm sources or propagated from existing Cuban Fiberless trees internationally"}, {"name": "Bennett (Costa Rican Selection) 🏆", "slug": "bennett-costa-rican-selection", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 13, "origin": "Costa Rica, 1920 - named for G.S. Bennett, Agricultural Superintendent of United Fruit Company''s Costa Rican Division", "traits": "Large, handsome fruit, described by Dr. Wilson Popenoe as most fruitful tree seen", "flesh_fruit": "Excellent quality, superior characteristics for commercial production", "yield_notes": "Exceptional productivity - most fruitful soursop tree documented in 1920", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Indonesian Selections (Sirsak)", "slug": "indonesian-selections-sirsak", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 14, "origin": "Indonesia - world''s largest soursop producer", "traits": "Diverse selections adapted to Indonesian tropical conditions, variable fruit size and shape", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet-fruited and sour-fruited types available, quality varies by selection", "yield_notes": "Indonesia produces hundreds of thousands of tons annually, indicating excellent productivity", "growing_notes": "Indonesia is world''s TOP soursop producer with optimal growing conditions. Major production regions: Java, Sumatra, Bali, Sulawesi, Kalimantan. Tropical climate with fertile volcanic soil creates ideal conditions. Trees propagated using seeds or grafting, with grafted plants offering earlier fruiting. Extensive post-harvest handling expertise. Climate highly similar to tropical monsoon climates - tropical, high rainfall, fertile soil. Indonesian cultivation practices directly applicable to tropical monsoon climates production.", "availability": "May be available through Indonesian agricultural institutions or Southeast Asian germplasm exchange"}, {"name": "Thai Selections (Thurian Thet/Thurian Khaek)", "slug": "thai-selections-thurian-thet-thurian-khaek", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 15, "origin": "Thailand", "traits": "Thai selections adapted to Southeast Asian tropical conditions", "flesh_fruit": "Used extensively in Thai desserts, ice creams, and beverages", "yield_notes": "Produced primarily for domestic consumption and regional export", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Malaysian Selections (Durian Belanda)", "slug": "malaysian-selections-durian-belanda", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 16, "origin": "Malaysia", "traits": "Malaysian selections with tropical adaptation", "flesh_fruit": "Quality characteristics suited to fresh consumption and processing", "yield_notes": "Contributes to regional production, smaller scale than Indonesia", "growing_notes": "Malaysia grows soursop on smaller scale than Indonesia but with similar climate advantages. Tropical climate with high humidity and rainfall year-round. Well-drained soil requirements similar to tropical monsoon climates conditions. Southeast Asian cultivation experience valuable for tropical monsoon climates growers. Climate characteristics closely match tropical monsoon climates monsoon patterns.", "availability": "May be available through Malaysian agricultural institutions or regional exchanges"}, {"name": "Vietnamese Selections (Mang Cau Xiem)", "slug": "vietnamese-selections-mang-cau-xiem", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 17, "origin": "Vietnam", "traits": "Vietnamese tropical adaptations", "flesh_fruit": "Quality suited to Vietnamese fresh fruit markets", "yield_notes": "Supports local and regional markets", "growing_notes": "Vietnam cultivates soursop with tropical monsoon climate matching tropical monsoon climates. Strong agricultural sector with tropical fruit expertise. Climate includes distinct wet season with heavy rainfall similar to tropical monsoon climates monsoon. High humidity and warm temperatures year-round. Vietnamese cultivation techniques applicable to tropical monsoon climates conditions.", "availability": "May be available through Vietnamese agricultural institutions"}, {"name": "Mexican Selections (Guanabana)", "slug": "mexican-selections-guanabana", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 18, "origin": "Mexico - world''s leading producer and exporter", "traits": "Diverse selections optimized for commercial production and export, variable fruit sizes", "flesh_fruit": "Quality optimized for frozen pulp production and fresh fruit export", "yield_notes": "Leading world production with advanced cultivation techniques", "growing_notes": "Mexico is WORLD''S LEADING PRODUCER and primary exporter of soursop products (frozen pulp and fresh fruit). Extensive commercial cultivation experience and advanced production techniques. Main season June-September in Mexican growing regions. While some Mexican regions are drier than tropical monsoon climates, coastal tropical areas have similar conditions. Mexican germplasm represents commercial-quality selections with proven export standards. Expertise in post-harvest handling and processing valuable for tropical monsoon climates production development.", "availability": "May be available through Mexican agricultural institutions or major commercial nurseries"}, {"name": "Puerto Rican Selections 🏆", "slug": "puerto-rican-selections", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 19, "origin": "Puerto Rico - 14 distinct types cataloged by Agricultural Experiment Station", "traits": "Wide range cataloged: sweet, sub-acid, and acid types; subdivided by shape (round, heart-shaped, oblong, angular); further classified by flesh consistency (soft/juicy to firm/dry)", "flesh_fruit": "Variable - from soft and juicy to firm and comparatively dry", "yield_notes": "Historical production of 99,790 kg in 1977, indicating significant cultivation", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "FIRST CHOICE: Mullatha/Mullu Chakka (indigenous) - perfectly adapted, medicinal value, local availability", "slug": "first-choice-mullatha-mullu-chakka-indigenous-perfectly-adapted-medicinal-value-local-availability", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 20, "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}], "variety_count": 28}'::jsonb,
